First, we will convert the assets into dollars:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Value in \$} &= \dfrac{\text{Value in solaris}}{\text{Exchange Rate}}\\[10pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{39,250 solaris}}{\text{1.54 solaris}}\\[10pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 25,487.02}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The value of assets when converted into dollars is **$25,487.02**.

Next, we will convert the liabilities into dollars:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Value in \$} &= \dfrac{\text{Value in solaris}}{\text{Exchange Rate}}\\[10pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{12,000 solaris}}{\text{1.54 solaris}}\\[10pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 7,792.21}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The value of liabilities when converted into dollars is **$7,792.21**.

Lastly, we will convert the equity into dollars:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Value in \$} &= \dfrac{\text{Value in solaris}}{\text{Exchange Rate}}\\[10pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{27,250 solaris}}{\text{1.54 solaris}}\\[10pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 17,694.81}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The value of equity when converted into dollars is **$17,694.81**.
